WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.940
So I'm going to talk about what is the benefit of using SIFTOM and even combination with

00:00:05.940 --> 00:00:10.060
acetylene and venetoclasts in newly diagnosed MPN1 AML.

00:00:10.780 --> 00:00:12.000
My disclosures.

00:00:12.480 --> 00:00:18.460
So a very important point is related to the responses, how the MPN1 is behaving when the

00:00:18.460 --> 00:00:23.160
patients are responding, and what is the influence of venetoclasts in the treatment.

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:28.820
As we already know, in the relapse setting, MPN1 specifically does not impact the duration,

00:00:28.820 --> 00:00:34.200
the overall survival, even if MPN1 is mutated versus unmutated.

00:00:34.680 --> 00:00:39.820
But the addition of venetoclasts certainly is improving the overall survival, even with

00:00:39.820 --> 00:00:42.720
intensive chemotherapy versus no intensive chemotherapy.

00:00:42.920 --> 00:00:48.800
This is very likely influenced by the high expression of VCL2 proteins in MPN1 mutated

00:00:48.800 --> 00:00:52.000
AML, but there are certainly some challenges.

00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:57.340
One of them is that MPN1 many times comes with other mutations, commutations that could

00:00:57.340 --> 00:00:58.800
potentially be associated.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:02.920
So this is a very important point in terms of what is associated with relapse, even if

00:01:02.920 --> 00:01:08.460
the patients are treated in the adfront setting with venetoclasts, for which a couple of questions

00:01:08.460 --> 00:01:09.780
that I consider relevant.

00:01:10.180 --> 00:01:17.120
Can we achieve the cure combining many inhibitors with venetoclasts in the setting of triplets?

00:01:17.120 --> 00:01:23.580
And second, how can we come over relapses specifically related to chronic evolution or

00:01:23.580 --> 00:01:24.820
secondary AML?

00:01:24.820 --> 00:01:28.660
So this slide has been already reviewed by my expert colleagues.

00:01:28.660 --> 00:01:32.240
But I just want to point out two questions.

00:01:32.240 --> 00:01:35.680
Why is it important to consider many inhibitors in the front line settings?

00:01:35.760 --> 00:01:42.780
We already have historically curative options with intensive chemotherapy alone or HMA venetoclasts,

00:01:42.780 --> 00:01:47.280
specifically because there is a biological target that makes a lot of sense.

00:01:47.620 --> 00:01:52.880
The HOX, MACE, and ONE driven, and that is extremely many independent.

00:01:53.320 --> 00:01:58.240
The expression of VCL2, that is highly frequent in patients with MPN1.

00:01:58.240 --> 00:01:58.480
And the expression of VCL2, that is highly frequent in patients with MPN1.

00:01:58.480 --> 00:01:58.500
And the expression of VCL2, that is highly frequent in patients with MPN1.

00:01:58.500 --> 00:02:04.820
That could potentially achieve the deeper remission and durability of responses and

00:02:04.820 --> 00:02:05.820
the possibility of cure.

00:02:05.820 --> 00:02:09.800
And in the relapsed refractory setting, because there is already data, as my colleagues are

00:02:09.800 --> 00:02:15.780
demonstrating, in different many inhibitors when the patient has relapsed disease.

00:02:15.780 --> 00:02:19.140
But in newly diagnosed cases, what is ongoing?

00:02:19.140 --> 00:02:23.100
I mean, this is a data that my colleague, Dr. Robles, presented in December.

00:02:23.100 --> 00:02:25.760
It was one of the co-authors of the study.

00:02:25.760 --> 00:02:28.340
This was a study that was presented in 40 patients.

00:02:28.340 --> 00:02:30.760
It was a study that was presented in 40 patients where there is results from the phase 1B,

00:02:31.220 --> 00:02:34.580
where patients got treatment with monotherapy,

00:02:34.880 --> 00:02:38.560
where siftomany, 600 milligrams orally daily,

00:02:39.140 --> 00:02:43.000
starting cycle 1, day 8, and then continuously thereafter,

00:02:43.560 --> 00:02:47.080
in combination with azacitidine for seven days and venetoplax,

00:02:47.240 --> 00:02:49.860
somewhere between 14 to 28 days.

00:02:51.180 --> 00:02:54.140
The endpoints were CR and adverse events.

00:02:54.140 --> 00:02:57.940
The baseline characteristics, the majority of the patients were,

00:02:58.180 --> 00:03:05.980
there is a predominancy of white population, performance status 2 or below 2,

00:03:06.280 --> 00:03:11.160
and there were a high proportion of patients with commutations, with FLT3 and IDH mutations.

00:03:11.460 --> 00:03:13.860
There were no patients with therapy-related AML.

00:03:14.580 --> 00:03:17.860
In terms of the safety, very similar to other many inhibitors,

00:03:18.160 --> 00:03:22.820
predominantly two potential points, neutropenias, thrombocytopenias,

00:03:22.820 --> 00:03:28.020
talking about cytopenias in those exposed with triplets, followed by sepsis, neutropenic fever,

00:03:28.020 --> 00:03:32.180
that was present in a very low proportion of cases.

00:03:32.640 --> 00:03:37.040
More importantly, the adverse events associated with many inhibitors related

00:03:37.040 --> 00:03:40.640
to QT prolongation of differentiation syndrome were really very low,

00:03:40.640 --> 00:03:44.560
3% in each case, and only one showing QT prolongation.

00:03:46.520 --> 00:03:53.280
The clinical activities shown here, 86% of the patients responded with overall response rate of 89%.

00:03:53.280 --> 00:03:57.860
If we split the responses according to commutations, those with IDH mutations,

00:03:57.860 --> 00:04:03.880
had 89% responses versus 77% in those who had commutations with FLT3.

00:04:04.980 --> 00:04:08.900
The duration of treatment, and this is on a median follow-up of 26-point weeks,

00:04:09.180 --> 00:04:10.120
was not rich.

00:04:10.440 --> 00:04:12.620
The median overall survival was not rich.

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:17.420
There were a proportion of MPN1 patients that were able to proceed with transplant,

00:04:17.860 --> 00:04:23.260
and 68% of the patients were able to continue to be alive and continue the study.

00:04:23.940 --> 00:04:26.860
In conclusion, there were high response rates.

00:04:27.700 --> 00:04:30.140
This is a clinical institution study that was presented by Andy Anderson,

00:04:30.560 --> 00:04:34.240
combining that with HMA venetoclax, showing similar responses.

00:04:34.760 --> 00:04:38.600
There is another study that combined ribomini with HMA venetoclax

00:04:38.600 --> 00:04:45.080
that was presented at JCO by Dr. Seiner, where the responses were relatively similar, 85%.

00:04:45.080 --> 00:04:51.820
The combination of sistomini with A7 did not result in increased toxicity, as I already showed,

00:04:52.360 --> 00:04:56.180
and there is a randomized clinical trial with comment 017.

00:04:57.540 --> 00:05:02.360
As part of the key takeaways, I just want to bring some unmet needs

00:05:02.360 --> 00:05:06.320
and perhaps questions for my expert colleagues.

00:05:06.920 --> 00:05:11.020
First of all, the combination, the triplet, is very effective.

00:05:11.620 --> 00:05:17.120
More importantly, there is achievement of MRD, and there is MRD evaluated by NGS,

00:05:17.640 --> 00:05:19.300
and MRD with RT-PCR.

00:05:19.700 --> 00:05:21.600
The combination is well-tolerated.

00:05:21.600 --> 00:05:27.300
There are ongoing phase distress, not only limited to sistomini, but ribomini as a part of the,

00:05:27.380 --> 00:05:31.400
HOBON, EVOL2, or sistomini A7 as comment 017.

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:33.240
But there are unmet needs.

00:05:33.520 --> 00:05:38.400
Certainly, we need more real-world data, specifically safety, differentiation syndrome,

00:05:38.660 --> 00:05:42.480
QT prolongation in regular population, elderly patients.

00:05:42.860 --> 00:05:44.820
How to overcome the MEN1 resistant?

00:05:45.380 --> 00:05:49.340
How to overcome those cases that already failed venetoclax and continue,

00:05:49.500 --> 00:05:52.140
unfortunately, not responding to the treatment?

00:05:52.140 --> 00:05:57.220
What is the impact of more deep, ultrasensitive MRD techniques

00:05:57.220 --> 00:05:58.220
in treatment decisions?

00:05:58.220 --> 00:06:01.880
Specifically, we are considering a patient transplant candidate or no.

00:06:02.200 --> 00:06:06.740
And something that I certainly would like the guidance from my colleagues is how

00:06:06.740 --> 00:06:11.100
to use this sequentially, you know, what many inhibitor starts first,

00:06:11.100 --> 00:06:13.060
and what many inhibitor to start later.

00:06:13.060 --> 00:06:15.180
Thank you very much for your time.
